@page "/projects/TheMysteryOfHistoricalHeritage"

@using MeirellescPortfolio.Components

<PageTitle>@((MarkupString)StringLocalizer!["Title_TheMystery"].Value)</PageTitle>

<MudContainer MaxWidth="MaxWidth.Medium">

    <MudText Align="Align.Center"
             Typo="Typo.h5"
             Style="text-transform: uppercase;"
             Class="my-16">

        The Mystery Of Historical Heritage

    </MudText>

    <MudDivider />

    <MudGrid Class="my-16 d-block justify-center gap-x-2"
             Style="text-align:center">

        <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Outlined.VideogameAsset"/>

        <MudText Align="Align.Center"
                 Typo="Typo.h6">

            Game - Mobile

        </MudText>

    </MudGrid>

    <MudImage Src="/assets/projects/theMystery/banner2Blur.png"
              Style="width: 100%;" />

    <MudGrid Class="py-16 px-2 gap-y-2">

        <MudItem xs="12" Class="align-content-center">
            <MudText Align="Align.Center"
                     Typo="Typo.h6"
                     Style="text-transform: uppercase;">

                Story
            </MudText>
        </MudItem>

        <MudItem xs="12" Style="height:auto">

            <MudText Align="Align.Justify"
                     Typo="Typo.body1"
                     Class="d-inline-flex flex-column">

                Some day in the city of São Bernardo do Campo (SBC), dawned with an unusual light in the sky. Something strange happened that morning and all the villagers lost their memory! No one remembers the city's heritage anymore and why they are on the streets of their neighborhoods. They don't even remember their own names! Of all the residents, only three people did not suffer any memory loss: Stenio, Vera and Jé. One of these people is responsible for the memory blackout in the city of SBC and the player must find out who is the villain in this story.
                
                <br /><br />

                For that, the player must explore the city map and visit places that have or are historical heritage in search of clues, in addition to carrying out small missions (challenges) to help the city return to its routine.

                <br /><br />

                Throughout his journey of knowledge and investigation, the player will discover that there is a failure in the blackout that made the memory of an entire city disappear: the more he knows and explores the city's historical heritage in search of clues, the more the player will help to recover the lost memory of the residents.
            </MudText>
        </MudItem>
    </MudGrid>

    <MudGrid Class="py-16 px-2 gap-y-2">
        <MudItem xs="12" Class="align-content-center">
            <MudText Align="Align.Center"
                     Typo="Typo.h6"
                     Style="text-transform: uppercase;">

                Map
            </MudText>
        </MudItem>

        <MudItem xs="12" Style="text-align:center">
            <MudImage Src="/assets/projects/theMystery/map.png"
                      Class="rounded-lg"
                      Style="width: 100%; max-width: 350px" />
        </MudItem>
    </MudGrid>

    <MudGrid Class="py-16 px-2 gap-y-2">

        <MudItem xs="12" Class="align-content-center">
            <MudText Align="Align.Center"
                     Typo="Typo.h6"
                     Style="text-transform: uppercase;">

                CHARACTERISTICS
            </MudText>
        </MudItem>

        <MudItem xs="12" Style="height:auto">

            <MudText Align="Align.Justify"
                     Typo="Typo.body1"
                     Class="d-inline-flex flex-column">

                To encourage engagement and keep the player's attention throughout the game, we'll use elements such as:

                <br /><br />

                » Tracking progress in the game through the map and the diary;<br />
                » Collecting items (clues) to provide a sense of achievement and encourage the player to look for the next item in the game;<br />
                » Independent minigames to “break” the heritage content into small parts, facilitating cognitive assimilation and supporting the learning process;<br />
                » Different levels of difficulty in the mini games to contemplate different player profiles and make the player feel continually challenged and motivated;<br />
                » Surprise elements as a narrative resource to leverage the player's attention;

            </MudText>
        </MudItem>
    </MudGrid>

    <MudDivider />

    <MudGrid Class="py-16 pb-8 px-2 gap-y-2">
        <MudItem xs="12" Class="align-content-center">
            <MudText Align="Align.Center"
                     Typo="Typo.h6"
                     Style="text-transform: uppercase;">

                Main Character
            </MudText>
        </MudItem>

        <MudItem xs="12" Style="text-align:center">

            <MudImage Src="/assets/projects/theMystery/characterSprite.png"
                      Class="rounded-lg"
                      Style="width: 100%; max-width: 750px" />
        </MudItem>

        <MudItem xs="12" Class="align-content-center">
            <MudText Align="Align.Justify"
                     Typo="Typo.body1">

                Lorena, a 37-year-old adult woman, who is a saleswoman at a store in the city center. She also lost her memory during the blackout.
            </MudText>
        </MudItem>
    </MudGrid>

    <MudGrid Class="py-16 px-2 gap-y-2">
        <MudItem xs="12" Class="align-content-center">
            <MudText Align="Align.Center"
                     Typo="Typo.h6"
                     Style="text-transform: uppercase;">

                Screenshots
            </MudText>
        </MudItem>


        <MudItem xs="12" Style="text-align:start">
            <MudImage Src="/assets/projects/theMystery/SS1.png"
                      Style="width: 100%; max-width: 200px" />
        </MudItem>

        <MudItem xs="12" Style="text-align:center">
            <MudImage Src="/assets/projects/theMystery/SS2.png"
                      Class="rounded-lg"
                      Style="width: 100%; max-width: 200px" />
        </MudItem>

        <MudItem xs="12" Style="text-align:end">
            <MudImage Src="/assets/projects/theMystery/SS3.png"
                      Class="rounded-lg"
                      Style="width: 100%; max-width: 200px" />
        </MudItem>
    </MudGrid>

    <MudGrid Class="py-16 px-2 gap-y-2">
        <MudItem xs="12" Class="align-content-center">
            <MudText Align="Align.Center"
                     Typo="Typo.h6"
                     Style="text-transform: uppercase;">

                Softwares & Frameworks
            </MudText>
        </MudItem>


        <MudItem xs="12" Class="d-flex gap-x-8 justify-center">
            <MudImage Src="/assets/logos/Figma.png"
                      Class="rounded-lg"
                      Height="50" />

            <MudImage Src="/assets/logos/Photoshop.png"
                      Class="rounded-lg"
                      Height="50" />

            <MudImage Src="/assets/logos/Unity.png"
                      Class="rounded-lg"
                      Height="50" />

            <MudImage Src="/assets/logos/VisualStudio.png"
                      Class="rounded-lg"
                      Height="50" />
        </MudItem>

    </MudGrid>

    <MudDivider />

    <MudText Align="Align.Center"
             Typo="Typo.h6"
             Style="text-transform: uppercase;"
             Class="mt-16 mb-8">

        Thank You

    </MudText>

    <FooterCmpnt />

</MudContainer>


